text: Jean Whitehead (born 1937) is a female former athlete who competed for England. ==Athletics career== She represented England in the long jump at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. She was a member of the Liverpool Harriers & AC and aged just 18 established a new record of 18ft 9ins (5.71 m) in winning the Northern Senior title in 1955. ==References== Category:1937 births Category:Living people Category:English female long jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games
